Title: Series: Speculum Romanae Magnificentiae
Description: Face of an Egyptian canopic vase Etching
Curator's comments: This print is a pair with an impression showing the back of the vase. See impression at 1947,0319.26(96). Huelsen describes two editions of this print one with Claudio Duchetti's address and the other with Giovanni Orlandi's, but he does not mention the plate issued by Nicolas van Aelst. See comment for 1947,0319.26
Bibliographic references: Huelsen 1921 / Das Speculum Romanae Magnificentiae des Antonio Lafreri (125.b) (see curator's comment)
